name: Akroma, Angel of Wrath
text: Flying, first strike, vigilance, trample, haste, protection from black and from red
flavor: "Wrath is no vice when inflicted upon the deserving."

name: Icatian Priest
text: {1}{W}{W}: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: Grelden knelt and felt the cool, dry hand of the priest on his brow. Hours later, when his wits returned, he was covered in his enemies' blood on the field of victory.

name: Angelic Page
text: Flying\n{T}: Target attacking or blocking creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: If only every message were as perfect as its bearer.

name: Charging Paladin
text: Whenever Charging Paladin attacks, it gets +0/+3 until end of turn.
flavor: "Hope shall be the blade that severs our bonds."

name: Venerable Monk
text: When Venerable Monk enters the battlefield, you gain 2 life.
flavor: Age wears the flesh but galvanizes the soul.

name: Angelic Protector
text: Flying\nWhenever Angelic Protector becomes the target of a spell or ability, Angelic Protector gets +0/+3 until end of turn.
flavor: "My family sheltered in her light, the dark was content to wait."\n—Crovax

name: Serra Advocate
text: Flying\n{T}: Target attacking or blocking creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: An angel's blessing prepares a soldier for war better than a thousand military drills.

name: Sustainer of the Realm
text: Flying\nWhenever Sustainer of the Realm blocks, it gets +0/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: You may break her shield, but you'll never break her spirit.

name: Angel of Mercy
text: Flying\nWhen Angel of Mercy enters the battlefield, you gain 3 life.
flavor: Every tear shed is a drop of immortality.

name: Serra Angel
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nVigilance (Attacking doesn't cause this creature to tap.)
flavor: Her sword sings more beautifully than any choir.

name: Twilight Shepherd
text: Flying, vigilance\nWhen Twilight Shepherd enters the battlefield, return to your hand all cards in your graveyard that were put there from the battlefield this turn.\nPersist (When this creature dies, if it had no -1/-1 counters on it, return it to the battlefield under its owner's control with a -1/-1 counter on it.)

name: Luminous Angel
text: Flying\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you may put a 1/1 white Spirit creature token with flying onto the battlefield.
flavor: "The spread of evil's destruction shall always be matched by the rise of the noble fallen."

name: Reya Dawnbringer
text: Flying\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: "You have not died until I consent."

name: Healing Salve
text: Choose one —\n• Target player gains 3 life.\n• Prevent the next 3 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.

name: Angelsong
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
flavor: Clash of sword and cry of beast fall mute when angels sound the call to prayer.

name: Otherworldly Journey
text: Exile target creature. At the beginning of the next end step, return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control with a +1/+1 counter on it.
flavor: "The landscape shimmered and I felt a chill breeze. When my vision cleared, I found myself alone among the corpses of my fallen friends."\n—Journal found in Numai

name: Pacifism
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature can't attack or block.
flavor: Even those born to battle could only lay their blades at Akroma's feet.

name: Serra's Boon
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+2 as long as it's white. Otherwise, it gets -2/-1.
flavor: "The light of an angel's glance is warm, but her fixed stare blinds and burns."\n—Calexis, deacon of the New Order of Serra

name: Angelic Benediction
text: Exalted (Whenever a creature you control attacks alone, that creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.)\nWhenever a creature you control attacks alone, you may tap target creature.
flavor: "Even in single combat, I am never alone."\n—Rafiq of the Many

name: Faith's Fetters
text: Enchant permanent\nWhen Faith's Fetters enters the battlefield, you gain 4 life.\nEnchanted permanent's activated abilities can't be activated unless they're mana abilities. If enchanted permanent is a creature, it can't attack or block.

name: Serra's Embrace
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2 and has flying and vigilance.
flavor: The touch of Serra's angels bears hopes aloft and empowers noble causes.

name: Righteous Cause
text: Whenever a creature attacks, you gain 1 life.
flavor: "Until the world unites in vengeful fury and Phage is destroyed, I will not stay my hand."\n—Akroma, angelic avenger

name: Angel's Feather
text: Whenever a player casts a white spell, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: If taken, it cuts the hand that clutches it. If given, it heals the hand that holds it.

name: Marble Diamond
text: Marble Diamond enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {W} to your mana pool.

name: Secluded Steppe
text: Secluded Steppe enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {W} to your mana pool.\nCycling {W} ({W}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Lord of the Pit
text: Flying, trample\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice a creature other than Lord of the Pit. If you can't, Lord of the Pit deals 7 damage to you.
flavor: "My summoning begins your debt, planeswalker."

name: Abyssal Gatekeeper
text: When Abyssal Gatekeeper dies, each player sacrifices a creature.
flavor: "There are two ways for me to pass this gate. One involves you remaining conscious."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Foul Imp
text: Flying\nWhen Foul Imp enters the battlefield, you lose 2 life.
flavor: The imp, unaware of its own odor, paused to catch its breath . . . and promptly died.

name: Daggerclaw Imp
text: Flying\nDaggerclaw Imp can't block.
flavor: The Simic use the claws as scalpels, while the Rakdos use them for tattooing and torture. The Gruul use them to pick their teeth after lunching on the rest of the carcass.

name: Dusk Imp
text: Flying
flavor: Imps are just intelligent enough to have an understanding of cruelty.

name: Overeager Apprentice
text: Discard a card, Sacrifice Overeager Apprentice: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: Slow and steady may not always win the race, but at least it doesn't end up splattered on the walls.

name: Stinkweed Imp
text: Flying\nWhenever Stinkweed Imp deals combat damage to a creature, destroy that creature.\nDredge 5 (If you would draw a card, instead you may put exactly five cards from the top of your library into your graveyard. If you do, return this card from your graveyard to your hand. Otherwise, draw a card.)

name: Soot Imp
text: Flying\nWhenever a player casts a nonblack spell, that player loses 1 life.
flavor: "If one gets in your chimney, you're going to need a long wick and a barrel of bangstuff to get it out."\n—Hob Heddil

name: Demon's Jester
text: Flying\nHellbent — Demon's Jester gets +2/+1 as long as you have no cards in hand.
flavor: They knock 'em dead, with or without the punch line.

name: Souldrinker
text: Pay 3 life: Put a +1/+1 counter on Souldrinker.
flavor: Don't drink and thrive.

name: Abyssal Specter
text: Flying\nWhenever Abyssal Specter deals damage to a player, that player discards a card.
flavor: To gaze under its hood is to invite death.

name: Cackling Imp
text: Flying\n{T}: Target player loses 1 life.
flavor: Its laughter drives needles through your mind.

name: Fallen Angel
text: Flying\nSacrifice a creature: Fallen Angel gets +2/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "Why do you weep for the dead? I rejoice, for they have died for me."

name: Reiver Demon
text: Flying\nWhen Reiver Demon enters the battlefield, if you cast it from your hand, destroy all nonartifact, nonblack creatures. They can't be regenerated.

name: Kuro, Pitlord
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice Kuro, Pitlord unless you pay {B}{B}{B}{B}.\nPay 1 life: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.

name: Dark Ritual
text: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: "Leshrac, my liege, grant me the power I am due."\n—Lim-Dûl, the Necromancer

name: Duress
text: Target opponent reveals his or her hand. You choose a noncreature, nonland card from it. That player discards that card.
flavor: "Change your mind, or I'll change it for you."

name: Unholy Strength
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+1.
flavor: Such power grows the body as it shrinks the soul.

name: Cruel Edict
text: Target opponent sacrifices a creature.
flavor: "Choose your next words carefully. They will be your last."\n—Phage the Untouchable

name: Demonic Tutor
text: Search your library for a card and put that card into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Liliana learned the secrets she sought, but at a price that was etched on her fate.

name: Dark Banishing
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor:
"Ha, banishment? Be merciful, say ‘death,'
For exile hath more terror in his look,
Much more than death."
—William Shakespeare, Romeo and Juliet

name: Oni Possession
text:
Enchant creature
At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice a creature.
Enchanted creature gets +3/+3 and has trample.
Enchanted creature is a Demon Spirit.

name: Barter in Blood
text: Each player sacrifices two creatures.
flavor: "In the game of conquest, who cares about the pawns if the king yet reigns?"\n—Geth, keeper of the Vault

name: Breeding Pit
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice Breeding Pit unless you pay {B}{B}.\nAt the beginning of your end step, put a 0/1 black Thrull creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: The thrulls bred at a terrifying pace. In the end, they overwhelmed the Order of the Ebon Hand.

name: Promise of Power
text:
Choose one —
• You draw five cards and you lose 5 life.
• Put an X/X black Demon creature token with flying onto the battlefield, where X is the number of cards in your hand.
Entwine {4} (Choose both if you pay the entwine cost.)

name: Corrupt
text: Corrupt deals damage equal to the number of Swamps you control to target creature or player. You gain life equal to the damage dealt this way.
flavor: There are things beneath the murk for whom the bog is a stew, a thin broth in need of meat.

name: Consume Spirit
text: Spend only black mana on X.\nConsume Spirit deals X damage to target creature or player and you gain X life.
flavor: "Your blood, your marrow, your spirit—all are mine."\n—Mayvar, minion of Geth

name: Demon's Horn
text: Whenever a player casts a black spell, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: Its curve mimics the twists of life and death.

name: Barren Moor
text: Barren Moor enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {B} to your mana pool.\nCycling {B} ({B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

text: Flying

text: Flying
